A worker came to fix the kitchen floor, and I pretended to be working from home, but in reality, I was editing "Unhooked."
If only this damned file could open. (OneDrive is truly a piece of垃圾.)
*The hacker's voice* I'm in.
He started drilling, and the sound was super loud. Great.
Turn the air purifier to maximum, which felt a bit too aggressive, but I did smell the wood shavings, so it was justified, especially since he opposed wearing masks. And I really did need to protect myself, didn't I?
I really wanted to go back to sleep, but I couldn't sleep until he left.
Good news is that Chapter Four is finally edited!
Chapter Five is really long and makes me super anxious. Yay! It's so exciting!
Looking up and replacing... ➡️ ellipsis, there are 54 of them in this chapter 😅
But I still insist on this point. Most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally agitated.
The floor repair worker is using a vacuum cleaner to clean up, hoping this means he's about to finish.
He went out (it sounded like) cutting something. I secretly checked the progress. There's still a lot of work to do : (
Chapter Five still has seven pages left. This is still my favorite chapter, and the draft is in pretty good shape—mostly just some formatting adjustments and minor tweaks to active voice and conciseness. But I really need a break, to have a cup of tea, while that guy is still messing around in my kitchen.
He started using the vacuum cleaner again. Hoping this is a good sign.
The kitchen floor repair worker is gone!
He told me he quoted the price for repairing the entire floor, but the landlord is too stingy and only willing to pay for the damaged section at the entrance. It feels much better now.
I'm having tea in the garden while the air purifier is working hard in the kitchen, purifying the air in the room!
